Privacy Policy for Eve

Last Updated: 9/11/2024

Welcome to Eve, a social media and e-commerce platform that connects people through chat, posts, and reels, and provides shopping experiences. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, share, and protect your information when you use our app, Eve.

1. Information We Collect

We collect various types of information to provide a better user experience, improve our services, and ensure the security of our platform.

1.1 Personal Information
When you register or use Eve, we collect the following personal information:

Contact Information: Your name, email address, phone number, and username.
Demographic Information: Your date of birth, gender, and location.
Account Information: Profile photo, preferences, and interests.
Social Media Information: If you register using Google, Facebook, or Apple, we may collect your public profile information from those platforms.
Location Information: Real-time location data to provide map services, location-based content, and relevant advertisements.
E-commerce Information: Payment details, purchase history, and shipping address when you make transactions on the app.
1.2 Technical Information
We automatically collect certain technical information, including:

Device Information: Device type, operating system, and unique device identifiers.
Log Information: IP address, browser type, access times, and pages viewed.
Usage Information: Information about how you use our app, including your interactions with posts, reels, and other users.
2. How We Use Your Information

We use the information we collect for the following purposes:

2.1 Providing and Improving Services

To create and manage your account.
To personalize your experience by showing you content and ads relevant to your interests.
To facilitate social media functions, including sharing, chatting, and connecting with other users.
To enable e-commerce transactions and provide customer support.
2.2 Communication

To send you updates, promotional materials, and notifications related to your use of Eve.
To respond to your inquiries and provide support.
2.3 Security and Compliance

To monitor and ensure the security of the app, protect against fraud, and enforce our terms of service.
To comply with applicable legal obligations and respond to requests from public authorities.
3. How We Share Your Information

We may share your information with third parties under the following circumstances:

3.1 Service Providers
We work with third-party service providers to perform certain functions on our behalf, such as payment processing, data analysis, email delivery, hosting services, and customer support.

3.2 Social Media Platforms
If you choose to register or log in using Google, Facebook, or Apple, we may share certain information with these platforms to facilitate registration and login processes.

3.3 Business Transfers
If we are involved in a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, your information may be transferred as part of that business transaction.

3.4 Legal Requirements
We may disclose your information to comply with applicable laws, regulations, legal processes, or governmental requests.

4. Your Choices and Rights

4.1 Account Information
You can update, correct, or delete your account information at any time through your account settings in the app.

4.2 Marketing Communications
You can opt-out of receiving promotional communications from us by following the unsubscribe instructions in the emails or by changing your preferences in the app settings.

4.3 Data Rights
Depending on your location, you may have certain rights under applicable data protection laws, including the right to access, correct, delete, or restrict the processing of your personal data.

5. Security of Your Information

We implement reasonable security measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction. However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is completely secure, so we cannot guarantee absolute security.

6. Retention of Your Information

We retain your personal information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes described in this Privacy Policy unless a longer retention period is required or permitted by law.

7. Childrenâ€™s Privacy

Eve is not intended for use by children under the age of 13. If we learn that we have collected personal information from a child under 13, we will take steps to delete such information promptly.

8. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or for other operational, legal, or regulatory reasons. If we make material changes, we will notify you by email or through a notice on our app.

9. Contact Us

If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us at:

Email: eveapp96@gmail.com
10. Your Consent

By using Eve, you consent to the collection, use, and sharing of your information as described in this Privacy Policy.
